Remove obsolete second wakeup_paused

commit.message: mention reviewer in changelog
Apply suggestion
Update deprecation comment version number
Update doc of abandon_yielded_and_paused
Update CHANGES after rebase
Deprecated unix's yield functions implemented as calls to Lwt.pause
document how to wait for one whole iteration of main loop

Remove obsolete second wakeup_paused

It was introduced in d5822af9a80b745515e0988541d7a43ed9a6faba.
If I understand it correctly this was done to prevent calling select
without timeout while there were pending paused promises.

Since now we explicitely check for this condition and call select with
zero timeout (`should_block_waiting_for_io`). This extra `wakeup_paused`
seems to be obsolete.
